abstract: Wisconsin election could profoundly reshape state's Supreme Court, which has been defined in recent years by polarization and reports of dysfunction; shift could hinge on whether voters re-elect liberal incumbent Ann Walsh Bradley over opponent James Daley, and whether they approve constitutional amendment that could result in installation of conservative chief justice.
lead_paragraph: Ahead of the vote on Tuesday, out-of-state money has poured in, and harsh advertisements have filled the airwaves.

headline.main: Wisconsin Supreme Court Election Raises Concerns About Partisanship
headline.print_headline: Partisanship a Worry in Wisconsin Supreme Court Election
